title: Bug 121170: get column label from meta data object should return some user recognizable strings
OB: The labels returned before extraction are null, while the ones after extraction are recognizable strings.
EB: Before the extraction process, when calling the 'getcolumnlabel' function from the meta data object, it should return the same user recognizable labels as after the extraction.
SR:
1. Perform an extraction process using the meta data object.
2. Call the 'getcolumnlabel' function from the meta data object before the extraction.
3. Verify that the returned labels are recognizable strings.
4. Repeat the same steps after the extraction and confirm that the labels remain the same.
